<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-22-1410 </DOCNO><TEXT>The major short term growth in biotechnology is occurring in pharmaceuticalsand agricultural chemicals. A shared effort between biochemical engineersand molecular biologists is necessary. Substrate cost and by-producteconomics of fuels, fermentation and enzymatic conversion of foodstuffs,organic intermediates, speciality chemicals and pharmaceuticals are discussedfrom the point of view of market potential, separation technology, efficiencyand safety. Investment costs are so enormous that only large companiescan bear the cost of process innovation. (Refs. 1).</TEXT></DOC>